race.description: Choices Flooring Seymour & Euroa Maiden Plate
race.comment: PARISH PRIEST (8) returned from a spell with a solid third over 1203m at Kyneton 17 days ago in his first run as a gelding. There is more depth to this field, but he is bred to be good, and his first win is not far away. POSITIVO (3) settled back from a wide gate last start and hit the line strongly to finish sixth over 1200m at Sandown-Lakeside. The extra 100m should suit him, and he could be charging late again. ITAZURA (7) closed well to grab third over 1000m at Moe when resuming, and was just under 3 lengths from the winner. He should strip fitter second-up, and the extra 300m will ensure that he will be right in the finish again. LOUIS BARTHAS (1) was third in a handy maiden field last time out, and will be peaking for this. Each way claims.
